      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must be version-controlled with documented regression testing suite covering at least 90% of relevant physics modules.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver is under version control and a regression suite exists, but coverage of hemolysis-relevant turbulence modules is documented at 72%, falling below the 90% threshold required at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Order-of-accuracy tests must be demonstrated for all governing equations used in the hemolysis model, including the scalar transport equation for the damage accumulation variable.",
      "rationale": "Order-of-accuracy tests were completed for momentum and continuity equations. The scalar transport equation for the power-law hemolysis damage variable was not independently verified; achieved level is therefore Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) reported for hemolysis index QOI at all five operating points with GCI < 5%.",
      "rationale": "GCI was computed at three of five operating points. At operating points 2 and 4, only two grid levels were available; Richardson extrapolation was not possible and GCI is unreported. Achieved level capped at 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (inlet flow waveform, outlet pressure, fluid temperature) must be fully characterized and replicated in the simulation to within 2% deviation.",
      "rationale": "Inlet flow and outlet pressure were matched within 2%. Fluid temperature during experiments was recorded as nominal 37 °C but was not continuously logged; peak deviations of up to 1.8 °C are noted in the lab record, introducing unquantified viscosity uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E% or validation uncertainty U_val) must be reported for each QOI at each operating point, with statistical confidence intervals.",
      "rationale": "E% was reported for all five operating points. However, confidence intervals were only computed for operating points 1, 3, and 5 where Monte Carlo UQ was fully propagated. Operating points 2 and 4 lack confidence interval estimates; the comparison is therefore incomplete."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The primary QOI (hemolysis index, HI) must be directly clinically relevant and mapped to a measurable plasma free hemoglobin endpoint.",
      "rationale": "The hemolysis index QOI is directly mapped to plasma free hemoglobin (pfHb) via the modified power-law model of Giersiepen et al. and is the standard clinical surrogate. Relevance is well established in the literature and accepted by FDA guidance."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must use the same pump geometry, fluid (bovine blood or equivalent), and operating envelope as the COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments used the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry and bovine blood analog. However, the VAD operating envelope extends to 6 LPM / 5000 RPM, while the experimental dataset covers only up to 5 LPM / 4500 RPM at full characterization. Extrapolation at the highest operating point reduces relevance."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence must be demonstrated to residual norms below 1e-5 for all equations at all operating points.",
      "rationale": "Residuals for momentum and continuity reached 1e-5 at all operating points. The hemolysis scalar transport residual stalled at approximately 1e-4 at operating points 2 and 4, indicating incomplete iterative convergence for the primary QOI equation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "A documented simulation execution checklist must be completed and reviewed by an independent analyst for each operating point simulation.",
      "rationale": "A simulation checklist was used for operating points 1, 3, and 5. For operating points 2 and 4, the checklist was completed by the same analyst who performed the simulation without independent review, failing the independence requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The hemolysis model form (constitutive equations, turbulence model, damage accumulation law) must be justified by published validation studies at comparable Reynolds number and shear stress regimes.",
      "rationale": "The k-omega SST turbulence model is used. Published validation references support its use at moderate Reynolds numbers; however, the VAD impeller tip speed generates localized regions with Re > 1e6 where SST has limited validation evidence. The power-law damage accumulation model is used without recalibration to bovine blood data, relying on human blood coefficients from Giersiepen et al. Model form uncertainty is substantial."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters must have documented sources with uncertainty bounds; sensitivity analysis must identify the top three inputs by influence on HI.",
      "rationale": "Blood viscosity, density, and pump rotational speed are documented with uncertainty bounds. The power-law exponent alpha and coefficient C in the hemolysis model are taken from literature without uncertainty characterization. Sensitivity analysis was performed but did not include alpha and C as free parameters, underestimating their influence on HI."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At least three independent blood sample batches must be used across experimental replicates to characterize inter-batch variability in hemolysis measurements.",
      "rationale": "Experiments were performed using two bovine blood batches. A third batch was planned but not available within the study timeline. Inter-batch variability is therefore undercharacterized relative to the MRL 5 requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation input parameters must be demonstrated equivalent to experimental conditions via a formal parameter matching table with documented tolerances.",
      "rationale": "A parameter matching table was produced for operating points 1, 3, and 5. For operating points 2 and 4, the matching table was omitted from the validation report. Equivalency cannot be confirmed for those conditions without the formal documentation."
